<subSubSection id="1FFC6501BD6EFFFFFB05FDEDE8EDFB84" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="5759368ABD6EFFFFFB05FDEDE8EDFB84" blockId="1.[810,1452,516,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFB05FDEDEFCDFDAA" bold="true" box="[810,921,516,542]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Material.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="885D8828BD6EFFFFFB87FDECE84CFDAB" box="[936,1048,517,543]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Lectotype</typeStatus>
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFC08FDECE8E8FDAB" box="[1063,1212,517,543]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM18623" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFC08FDECE833FDAB" box="[1063,1127,517,543]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
18623
</accessionNumber>
(a nearly complete wasp) (
<figureCitation id="CFDD2A0FBD6EFFFFFB55FDC1EFEDFDF6" box="[890,953,552,578]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,235,1241,1265]" captionTargetBox="[138,1449,656,1218]" captionTargetId="figure-233@2.[138,1449,656,1218]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Tapholyda caplani (Cockerell, 1933), lectotype UCM 18623. A, Rock piece with the specimen. B, Photograph. Scale bars = 5 mm (A), 2 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530327" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530327/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Another specimen 
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFCB2FDC1E97CFDF7" box="[1181,1320,552,579]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM19165" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFCB2FDC1E889FDF6" box="[1181,1245,552,578]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
19165
</accessionNumber>
also has the label ‘Holotype’ in the collection database of the Museum of Natural History of 
<collectingRegion id="9522F868BD6EFFFFFC36FD87E8D5FD3C" box="[1049,1153,622,648]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Colorado</collectingRegion>
(https://invertpaleosearch. colorado.edu/), but its body length is 
<quantity id="901E9B6FBD6EFFFFFCC4FD78E902FD18" box="[1259,1366,657,684]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.54" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" unit="mm" value="15.4">15.4 mm</quantity>
, which does not correspond to the dimensions indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="33774B7BBD6EFFFFFB05FD31EFBFFD46" author="Cockerell, T. D. A." box="[810,1003,728,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" pagination="186 - 187" refId="ref4521" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1933) A fossil sawfly from the Miocene shales near Creede (Colorado). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 28, 186 - 187." type="journal article" year="1933">Cockerell (1933)</bibRefCitation>
. Notice that 
<bibRefCitation id="33774B7BBD6EFFFFFC5AFD31EFE0FCA2" author="Zhelokhovtsev, A. N. &amp; Rasnitsyn, A. P." pageId="1" pageNumber="174" pagination="315 - 327" refId="ref5695" refString="Zhelokhovtsev, A. N. &amp; Rasnitsyn, A. P. (1972) On some Tertiary sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) from Colorado. Psyche, 79, 315 - 327. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 1972 / 63630" type="journal article" year="1972">Zhelokhovtsev &amp; Rasnitsyn (1972: 326)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the 
<typeStatus id="885D8828BD6EFFFFFCB1FD12E954FCA1" box="[1182,1280,763,789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">holotype</typeStatus>
would be the specimen 
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFBB2FCF6E87BFC8C" box="[925,1071,798,825]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM18626" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFBB2FCF6EF89FC8D" box="[925,989,799,825]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
18626
</accessionNumber>
, but the fossil under this number in the collection is the 
<typeStatus id="885D8828BD6EFFFFFC6EFCABE8F7FCE8" box="[1089,1187,834,860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">holotype</typeStatus>
of the bug 
<taxonomicName id="90E64D09BD6EFFFFFD18FCABE867FCCB" authority="Kirkaldy, 1910" authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Poliocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amnesis">
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFD18FCABEFD0FCCB" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Poliocoris amnesis</emphasis>
Kirkaldy, 1910
</taxonomicName>
from Florissant (
<collectingRegion id="9522F868BD6EFFFFFCDAFC8CE930FC34" box="[1269,1380,869,896]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Colorado</collectingRegion>
). New specimens. 
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFB9DFC61E810FC17" box="[946,1092,904,931]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM35546" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFB9DFC61EFA6FC16" box="[946,1010,904,930]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
35546
</accessionNumber>
(a nearly complete specimen) (
<figureCitation id="CFDD2A0FBD6EFFFFFB1DFC42EF2BFC72" box="[818,895,939,966]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,189,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[145,1443,189,1742]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Tapholyda caplani (Cockerell, 1933), UCM 33546. A, Rock piece with the specimen. B, Photograph. C, Detailed photograph of left forewing. D, Detailed photograph of right forewing. E, Interpretative line drawing of forewing venation with vein and cell names labeled. Scale bars = 5 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C–E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), 
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFBB0FC45E861FC72" box="[927,1077,939,966]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM35549" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFBB0FC45EF8BFC72" box="[927,991,940,966]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
35549
</accessionNumber>
(a partly preserved specimen, tentatively assigned to this species) (
<figureCitation id="CFDD2A0FBD6EFFFFFCEBFC26E95DFC5D" box="[1220,1289,975,1001]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,904,928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,880]" captionTargetId="figure-501@4.[151,1436,189,880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Tapholyda caplani (Cockerell, 1933), UCM 35549. A, Rock piece with the specimen. B, Photograph of specimen. Scale bars = 10 mm (A), 5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530333/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), 
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFD31FC26E9FFFC5C" box="[1310,1451,974,1001]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM36942" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFD31FC26E90AFC5D" box="[1310,1374,975,1001]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
36942
</accessionNumber>
(a partly preserved specimen) (
<figureCitation id="CFDD2A0FBD6EFFFFFCB8FC1BE88BFBB9" box="[1175,1247,1010,1037]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[136,235,906,930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,882]" captionTargetId="figure-545@6.[151,1436,189,882]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Tapholyda caplani (Cockerell, 1933), UCM 36942. A, Photograph of imprint (a). B, Photograph of counterimprint (b). Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530339/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), 
<accessionNumber id="48B5AB69BD6EFFFFFCD6FC1BE9DEFBB9" box="[1273,1418,1010,1037]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/UCM35550" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="31F7AE4FBD6EFFFFFCD6FC1BE96DFBB8" box="[1273,1337,1010,1036]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34854" name="University of Colorado Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="University or college">UCM</collectionCode>
35550
</accessionNumber>
(a nearly complete specimen) (
