<subSubSection id="1FFC6501BD6EFFFCFB70FBD1EFF8FF6B" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5759368ABD6EFFFFFB70FBD1E979FBE7" blockId="1.[810,1452,516,2092]" box="[863,1325,1080,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFB70FBD1EF8DFBE6" bold="true" box="[863,985,1080,1106]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
As for the genus (
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFC88FBD1E949FBE6" box="[1191,1309,1080,1106]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">vide supra</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5759368ABD6EFFFFFB70FBB2E8D9FB6B" blockId="1.[810,1452,516,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFB70FBB2E826FBC1" bold="true" box="[863,1138,1115,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Oligocene, 
